Package org.odpi.openmetadata.frameworks.openmetadata.properties.informationsupplychains

package org.odpi.openmetadata.frameworks.openmetadata.properties.informationsupplychains
InformationSupplyChainProperties identifies a flow of data between systems in a digital landscape that are of importance to the organization. Each information supply chain is divided into segments (InformationSupplyChainSegmentProperties) that identify stages in the data flow. Typically, the segments show how the ownership changes along the supply chain. This may be caused by a change in technology, or the processing moves to a different part of the organization. The InformationSupplyChainLinks connect the segments together to show where data flows from/to. These are important hand off points for data.
